Setpoint for Cip forward changed to real from integer
CIP Program 1 = Rinse-caustic-rinse-acid-rinse-drain CIP Program 2 = rinse=caustic-rinse-drain
If the combi 512 is in fault, the CIP_PUMP_ON input is false, thus M0139 is de-engerised and the sequence is held. When the sequence is held steam and chemical valves are de-engerised.
Version 15 - 25/1/13 ...AFL Reset of "M_CAUSTIC_READY" ,"M_RINSE_READY", "M_ACID_READY", in step 1 after occurence of CIP going through without dosing any caustic into CIP solution.
Version 16 - 22/02/13 ...MC In addition to above comment, "CT_LYE_OK", "CT_ACID_OK" also reset in same step.
